    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-12T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-12T09:00:00-05:00" n="720"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.522/168: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Third Secretary of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wendelin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-12T14:00:00+00:00"
                            >September 12, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 12—1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>X–140. My telegram No. X–138, September 10, 7 p.m.<note n="29" xml:id="d720fn29"
                        >Not printed.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">Note verbale</hi>, from Ministry of State dated September 10
                    states that Spanish Government is making every effort to keep open official and
                    private communications and feels confident it can do so but that if unforeseen
                    causes should make this impossible this Embassy is authorized to use its radio,
                    first giving notice to that Ministry. I am now notifying Ministry of State that
                    radio operator from the <hi rend="italic">Quincy</hi> is attached to the Embassy
                    for the purpose of operating our radio equipment and requesting permission to
                    test transmission to make sure we can reach the <hi rend="italic">Quincy</hi> at
                    any time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wendelin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
